# Backend

## Tech Stack

| Layer | Technology |
|---|---|
| Language | Python 3.11 |
| Framework | FastAPI (latest) |
| Database | PostgreSQL (latest) |
| ORM | SQLAlchemy 2.x |
| Migrations | Alembic (latest) |
| Validation | Pydantic v2 + pydantic-settings |
| Auth | python-jose (JWT) + passlib (bcrypt) |
| Containerization | Docker + Docker Compose |

## Project Structure

```
{{ APP_NAME }}/
├── .env
├── .env.example
├── .gitignore
├── docker-compose.yml
└── server/
    ├── Dockerfile
    ├── requirements.txt
    ├── main.py
    ├── alembic.ini
    ├── alembic/
    │   ├── env.py
    │   └── versions/
    └── app/
        ├── api.py        ← central router, all modules registered under /api/v1
        ├── core/         ← config, database, security
        └── {{ MODULES }}/  ← one folder per module
```

Each module contains: `models.py`, `schemas.py`, `service.py`, `router.py`. Routers are thin — all business logic lives in services.

## Environment Variables

One `.env` file at project root. Both docker-compose and backend app read from it.

```env
POSTGRES_USER=
POSTGRES_PASSWORD=
POSTGRES_DB=
POSTGRES_HOST=postgres
POSTGRES_PORT=5432

SECRET_KEY=
JWT_ALGORITHM=HS256
JWT_EXPIRE_HOURS=24
```

## Docker Setup

### docker-compose.yml
- Services: `postgres`, `server`, `web` — container names must match service names exactly
- Pass env vars using `environment:` with `${VAR_NAME}` syntax — never use `env_file:`
- `server` depends on `postgres` with `condition: service_healthy`
- `web` depends on `server`
- Mount source folders as volumes for hot reload
- Always pin PostgreSQL to a specific major version e.g. `postgres:16-alpine` — never `postgres:latest`

### server/Dockerfile
- Base image: `python:3.11-slim`
- Install `gcc` and `libpq-dev` before pip install
- Copy and install `requirements.txt` before copying source code
- CMD:
```dockerfile
CMD ["uvicorn", "main:app", "--host", "0.0.0.0", "--port", "8000", "--reload", "--reload-dir", "app"]
```

## Architecture

### core/
- `config.py` — pydantic-settings `BaseSettings`, single `settings` instance, use `urllib.parse.quote_plus` on DB password when building `DATABASE_URL`
- `database.py` — SQLAlchemy engine, `Base`, `get_db` dependency
- `security.py` — bcrypt hash/verify, JWT create/decode

### Module structure
```
app/{{ MODULE }}/
    ├── models.py     ← SQLAlchemy models
    ├── schemas.py    ← Pydantic request/response schemas
    ├── service.py    ← all business logic as static methods
    └── router.py     ← thin, only calls service methods
```

### Authentication
Two auth methods — include both in every project:

**JWT — for human users**
- Login accepts JSON body `{ username, password }` → returns JWT token
- Passed as `Authorization: Bearer <token>` header
- `get_current_user` dependency in `app/auth/dependencies.py`

**API Keys — for programmatic access**
- Passed as `X-API-Key: <key>` header
- `get_user_by_api_key` dependency in `app/api_keys/dependencies.py`
- Key format: `{{ APP_NAME }}_` prefix + 32 char urlsafe random string
- Store only bcrypt hash + first 10 chars as prefix for fast DB lookup
- Show full key once on creation — never retrievable again
- Update `last_used` on every use

### Standard Endpoints
```
POST  /api/v1/auth/register
POST  /api/v1/auth/login
GET   /api/v1/auth/me

GET   /    → returns app name, version, status as JSON
```

## Alembic Migrations

### env.py rules
- Read credentials using `os.environ.get()` directly — never import `settings` or read `.env`
- Use `urllib.parse.quote_plus` on password when building DATABASE_URL
- Add project root to `sys.path` before importing any `app.*` modules
- Import all models so `--autogenerate` detects them

### Migration files
- Numbered sequentially: `001_`, `002_`, `003_`
- First migration has `down_revision = None`
- Every migration has both `upgrade()` and `downgrade()`
- One migration per table

### Running migrations — always manual, never on startup
```bash
docker exec server alembic upgrade head
docker exec server alembic current
docker exec server alembic downgrade -1
docker exec server alembic downgrade base
docker exec server alembic revision --autogenerate -m "description"
```

## Critical Rules — Backend

- Migrations run manually, never on startup
- Never use `Base.metadata.create_all()`
- Never use `env_file:` in docker-compose — use `environment:` with `${VAR}`
- Never store full API key — bcrypt hash + prefix only
- Always encode DB password with `quote_plus` in DATABASE_URL
- `alembic/env.py` reads from `os.environ` not `.env`
- Always use `--host 0.0.0.0` in uvicorn CMD
- Always use `--reload-dir app` in uvicorn CMD
- Always pin PostgreSQL to a specific major version — never `latest`
- Always include all required packages with their extras in `requirements.txt`
- Never name a SQLAlchemy model attribute `metadata` — reserved by `DeclarativeBase`. Use a different name and map explicitly e.g. `extra = Column("metadata", JSONB)`
- Never use `OAuth2PasswordRequestForm` — login always accepts JSON body
- Never use `Depends()` in both `Annotated` and default value — use `param: Type = Depends(...)` only
- GIN index on `text` column requires `pg_trgm` extension and `postgresql_ops` operator class
- GIN index on `JSONB` column uses default operator class — no extension needed
- Passwords must be truncated to 72 bytes before bcrypt hashing

