# Frontend

## Tech Stack

| Layer | Technology |
|---|---|
| Framework | React (latest) |
| Build Tool | Vite (latest) |
| UI Library | Ant Design / antd (latest) |
| HTTP Client | Axios (latest) |
| Routing | React Router (latest) |
| Forms | React Hook Form + Yup (latest) |
| Server State | TanStack Query / React Query (latest) |
| Date Handling | dayjs (bundled with Ant Design) |
| Styles | SCSS Modules |

Do not pin any package versions. Always use latest.

## Project Structure

```
web/
├── Dockerfile
├── index.html
├── vite.config.ts
├── package.json
├── .env
└── src/
    ├── main.tsx
    ├── App.tsx
    ├── constants/
    │   └── routes.ts        ← all route paths as constants
    ├── components/
    │   ├── form/
    │   │   ├── text_field.tsx
    │   │   └── select_field.tsx
    │   └── ui/              ← Spinner, EmptyState, etc.
    ├── hooks/               ← non-data-fetching hooks only
    ├── services/
    │   ├── axios.ts
    │   └── {{ MODULE }}.ts  ← API calls + React Query hooks co-located
    ├── types/
    │   └── user.ts          ← User type and other API entity types
    ├── pages/
    │   └── {{ page_name }}/ ← snake_case folder
    │       ├── index.ts              ← re-export default only
    │       ├── {{ page_name }}.tsx    ← page shell, layout only, no form logic
    │       ├── {{ page_name }}_f_orm.tsx ← extracted form component (if page has a form)
    │       ├── {{ page_name }}_table.tsx ← extracted table component (if page has a table)
    │       └── styles.module.scss      ← only if extra styles needed
    └── utils/
        └── token.ts         ← getToken, setToken, removeToken using key "access_token"
```

## Naming Conventions

| Thing | Convention | Example |
|---|---|---|
| Page folders | `snake_case` | `login/`, `api_keys/` |
| Component files | `snake_case` | `login.tsx`, `login_form.tsx` |
| Style / utility files | `snake_case` | `styles.module.scss`, `loader.module.scss` |
| Variables / hooks | `camelCase` | `isPending`, `useLogin` |
| Components | `PascalCase` | `LoginForm`, `TextField` |
| Interfaces | `PascalCase` with `I` prefix | `ITextField`, `ILoginRequest` |
| Sub-interfaces (nested types) | `PascalCase` with `I` prefix | `ISelectOption` |

## Interfaces
 
Every component **must** declare a named `I`-prefixed interface for its props. The component is declared as a `const` arrow function using that interface. This applies to all components — pages, form fields, UI components.
 
```tsx
// ✅ Correct
interface ITextField<T extends FieldValues> {
  control: Control<T>
  label: string
  name: Path<T>
  placeholder?: string
  type?: 'text' | 'email' | 'password'
}
 
export const TextField = <T extends FieldValues>({
  control,
  label,
  name,
  placeholder,
  type = 'text',
}: ITextField<T>) => { ... }
 
// ❌ Wrong — anonymous inline type, default export function style
export default function TextField({ label, name }: { label: string; name: string }) { ... }
```
 
All API entity types in `types/` also use the `I` prefix:
 
```ts
// types/user.ts
export interface IUser { ... }
export interface ILoginRequest { ... }
export interface ILoginResponse { ... }
```

## Docker Setup

### web/Dockerfile
```dockerfile
FROM node:lts-alpine
WORKDIR /app
COPY package*.json ./
RUN npm install
COPY . .
EXPOSE 3000
CMD ["npm", "run", "dev", "--", "--host", "0.0.0.0", "--port", "3000"]
```

Add to `.env`:
```env
VITE_API_URL=http://localhost:8000
```

## Architecture

### constants/routes.ts
All route paths as constants — never hardcode strings in components:
```ts
export const ROUTES = {
  LOGIN: '/login',
  DASHBOARD: '/dashboard',
} as const
```

### services/axios.ts
```ts
const instance = axios.create({ baseURL: import.meta.env.VITE_API_URL })

instance.interceptors.request.use((config) => {
  const token = localStorage.getItem('access_token')
  if (token) config.headers.Authorization = `Bearer ${token}`
  return config
})

instance.interceptors.response.use(
  (response) => response,
  (error) => {
    if (error.response?.status === 401) {
      localStorage.removeItem('access_token')
      window.location.href = ROUTES.LOGIN
    }
    return Promise.reject(error)
  }
)

export const get = <T>(url: string, params?: object) => instance.get<T>(url, { params }).then(r => r.data)
export const post = <T>(url: string, body?: object) => instance.post<T>(url, body).then(r => r.data)
export const put = <T>(url: string, body?: object) => instance.put<T>(url, body).then(r => r.data)
export const del = <T>(url: string) => instance.delete<T>(url).then(r => r.data)
```

### services/{{ MODULE }}.ts
API calls and React Query hooks co-located per module. Request/response param types defined inline. Only API entity types (e.g. `User`) go in `types/`.

### types/
Only types for data returned by the API. `user.ts` always exists:
```ts
// types/user.ts
export interface IUser {
  id: number
  username: string
  email: string
  isActive: boolean
  createdAt: string
}
```

### Form field components
Use Yup schema validation via `yupResolver` — never inline `rules` objects. No `rules` prop on field components.

**TextField**
```tsx
export const TextField = <T extends FieldValues>({
  name,
  control,
  label,
  type = 'text',
}: {
  name: Path<T>
  control: Control<T>
  label: string
  type?: string
}) => (
  <Controller
    name={name}
    control={control}
    render={({ field, fieldState }) => (
      <Form.Item
        label={label}
        validateStatus={fieldState.error ? 'error' : ''}
        help={fieldState.error?.message}
      >
        <Input {...field} type={type} />
      </Form.Item>
    )}
  />
)
```

**SelectField** — same wrapper pattern, uses Ant Design Select:
```tsx
export const SelectField = <T extends FieldValues>({
  name,
  control,
  label,
  options,
}: {
  name: Path<T>
  control: Control<T>
  label: string
  options: { label: string; value: string | number }[]
}) => (
  <Controller
    name={name}
    control={control}
    render={({ field, fieldState }) => (
      <Form.Item
        label={label}
        validateStatus={fieldState.error ? 'error' : ''}
        help={fieldState.error?.message}
      >
        <Select {...field} options={options} />
      </Form.Item>
    )}
  />
)
```

**Usage with Yup:**
```tsx
const schema = yup.object({
  username: yup.string().required('Username is required'),
  password: yup.string().min(6, 'Password must be at least 6 characters').required(),
})

type LoginFormValues = yup.InferType<typeof schema>

const { control, handleSubmit } = useForm<LoginFormValues>({
  resolver: yupResolver(schema),
})
```

### Pages
Each page is a folder. `index.tsx` default exports a component named same as the folder. Forms and tables are always separate components inside the page folder:

```
pages/
└── Login/
    ├── index.ts          ← export default Login
    ├── login.tsx         ← Login page
    └── login_form.tsx    ← form extracted as separate component

└── Users/
    ├── index.ts            ← export default Users
    ├── Users.tsx           ← Users page
    ├── users_table.tsx     ← table extracted as separate component
    ├── user_form.tsx       ← form extracted as separate component
    └── styles.module.scss
```

### Auth Flow
- JWT stored in localStorage under key `access_token`
- On app load: `useCurrentUser` checks localStorage, calls `/auth/me` to validate
- `ProtectedRoute` uses `useCurrentUser` — redirects to `ROUTES.LOGIN` if no valid user
- On logout: remove `access_token` from localStorage, call `queryClient.clear()`, redirect to `ROUTES.LOGIN`
- On 401: axios interceptor clears `access_token` and redirects to `ROUTES.LOGIN`

### QueryClientProvider
```tsx
const queryClient = new QueryClient()
<QueryClientProvider client={queryClient}><App /></QueryClientProvider>
```

## Critical Rules — Frontend

- Frontend folder is named `web/` not `client/`
- Use TypeScript for all files
- Use `import.meta.env.VITE_API_URL` — never hardcode localhost
- Every `useMutation` **must** have `onError` calling `message.error(...)`
- Every `useQuery` error must be surfaced via `message.error(...)`
- API functions are **not exported** — only hooks are exported
- Request/response param types are defined **inline** in the service file — only entity types (e.g. `IUser`) go in `types/`
- `invalidateQueries` must be called `onSuccess` when the mutation affects a list
- All route paths defined in `constants/routes.ts` — never hardcode route strings anywhere
- All API calls go through base functions in `services/axios.ts` — never use fetch or raw axios directly
- React Query hooks and API calls live in `services/{{ MODULE }}.ts` — not in `hooks/`
- `hooks/` is only for non-data-fetching hooks e.g. `useDebounce`, `useFilters`
- Request/response param types defined inline in service files — only API entity types go in `types/`
- `types/user.ts` always exists — `User` type always defined there
- All forms use React Hook Form with Yup schema via `yupResolver` — never inline `rules` objects
- No `rules` prop on `TextField` or `SelectField` — validation always comes from Yup schema
- Use `TextField` and `SelectField` from `components/form/` — never raw Ant Design inputs in pages
- If a page has a form, extract it as `{{ PageName }}Form.tsx` inside the page folder
- If a page has a table, extract it as `{{ PageName }}Table.tsx` inside the page folder
- All data fetching uses `useQuery` — no `useEffect + fetch` patterns
- All mutations use `useMutation` with `invalidateQueries` on success
- Never store server state in `useState` — React Query cache only
- JWT stored in localStorage under key `access_token`
- `ProtectedRoute` uses `useCurrentUser` from `services/auth.ts` — not a separate Context
- Each page is a folder — `index.ts` default exports a component named same as the folder
- Page-specific components live inside the page folder — shared/reusable components in `components/`
- Never use inline styles — use Ant Design components and props first, then `styles.module.scss` for additional styles
- Always use Ant Design components: `Flex`, `Space`, `Button`, `Table`, `Form`, `Input`, `Select` etc. — always give these priority over custom HTML elements
- Apply memoization where appropriate — `memo` for components, `useMemo` for derived values, `useCallback` for functions passed as props
- All tables use server-side pagination — pass `page` and `limit` to API, use `total` from response
- Ant Design `RangePicker` returns dayjs objects — convert with `.toISOString()` before sending to API
- Always ensure `vite.config.ts` and `package.json` are consistent — every plugin in `vite.config.ts` must be in `package.json`
- Always use the existing `eslint.config.js` flat config — never create `.eslintrc.cjs`
- ESLint required plugins: `eslint-plugin-import`, `eslint-plugin-jsx-a11y`, `eslint-import-resolver-typescript`
- Boolean props must use shorthand — `isOpen` not `isOpen={true}` (`react/jsx-boolean-value: never`)
- Props must be sorted alphabetically — shorthand booleans first, reserved props (key/ref) first, callbacks last
- Never use `../../` imports — maximum one level up `../` is allowed
- Parent imports `../` must appear before sibling imports `./` in import order
- Import groups order: builtin → external → internal → parent (`../`) → sibling (`./`) → styles
- Always add a newline between each import group